--- addendum: Fatemeh/LSST/dust layout (manual recon, the table row above is auto-mangled) ---
dust/4/{z0.0..z2.0, z0.3_issue}/{lsst_band}/kappa_2_9/{lsst_band} : per-star dust-attenuated
  apparent mags, f4. Star counts map each observed-z bin to a snapshot:
  z0.0->817, z0.1->771, z0.2->743, z0.3->743 (NOT 724!), z0.3_issue->724, z0.4->692, z0.5->660,
  z0.6->634, z0.7->609, z0.8->590, z0.9->567, z1.0->544, z1.1->523, z1.2->505, z1.3->483,
  z1.4->461, z1.5->440, z1.6->421, z1.7->403, z1.8->385, z1.9->367, z2.0->348.
dust/SubGroups/z0.5/SubGroups/{lsst_band} : per-subhalo dust mags, z0.5 ONLY.
dust/allbands_kappa2.9/z0.3 : present but contains no bigfile blocks (empty/incomplete).

--- addendum: Fatemeh 724-vs-743 data check ---
Fatemeh/LSST/PIG_724_photometric and PIG_743_photometric have IDENTICAL row counts (snapshot
743's catalog: 46,359,683 subhalos / 59.7e9 stars) but DIFFERENT data values (cmp differs at
byte 4) -> 724-named product = snapshot-743 galaxies at a different observed redshift, not a
copy. The real snapshot-724 catalog (46,940,435 subhalos) appears only in
Aperture/2_Stellar_half_mass/PIG_724_photometric and dust z0.3_issue.
